==English==

===Adjective===
'''seized'''
# ''(of goods):'' property that has been [[commandeer]]ed.
# ''(automotive):'' pertaining to a motor that no longer functions (internal parts fused together)

===Verb===
'''seized'''
# Past tense of ''to [[seize]].''
# {{intransitive}}, ''of a motor:'' no longer functioning as a result of internal moving components overheating past their [[melting point]], and subsequently fusing or welding themselves together.